Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) is considered a promising electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) due to its high ionic conductivity and stability under fuel cell operating conditions.
Titulo: Application of high velocity oxygen fuel flame (HVOF) spraying to fabrication of La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here we report our findings in investigating the feasibility of using a high velocity oxygen fuel flame (HVOF) spraying process for cost-effective fabrication of dense LSGM electrolyte membranes.
Titulo: Application of high velocity oxygen fuel flame (HVOF) spraying to fabrication of La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The flame and in-flight particle behavior were simulated numerically to optimize the microstructure and phase compositions of the LSGM deposits.
Titulo: Application of high velocity oxygen fuel flame (HVOF) spraying to fabrication of La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The measured gas leakage rate of an LSGM deposit is similar to 7 x 10(-7)

Sentencas: The single cell assembled with 50-55 mu m HVOF-sprayed LSGM electrolyte shows open circuit voltage (OCV) of 1.08 V at 800 degrees C, suggesting that the as-sprayed LSGM deposit is dense enough for direct application as SOFC electrolyte.
Titulo: Application of high velocity oxygen fuel flame (HVOF) spraying to fabrication of La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the ionic conductivity of the sprayed LSGM deposit is similar to 0.04 S cm(-1), indicating that the HVOF spraying is a promising process for low-temperature fabrication of dense LSGM electrolyte membranes for IT-SOFCs.
